				<div id="bodyContent" class="vector-body" aria-labelledby="firstHeading" data-mw-ve-target-container>
					<div class="vector-body-before-content">
							<div class="mw-indicators">
		</div>

						<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
					</div>
					<div id="contentSub"><div id="mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
					
					
					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Concept in mathematics</div>
<p>In <a href="/wiki/Numerical_optimization" class="mw-redirect" title="Numerical optimization">numerical optimization</a>, the <b>nonlinear conjugate gradient method</b> generalizes the <a href="/wiki/Conjugate_gradient_method" title="Conjugate gradient method">conjugate gradient method</a> to <a href="/wiki/Nonlinear_optimization" class="mw-redirect" title="Nonlinear optimization">nonlinear optimization</a>. For a quadratic function <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \displaystyle f(x)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
          <mi>f</mi>
          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        </mstyle>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \displaystyle f(x)}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/70218579209d1273fe59d0d5778f61a4a4597dc8" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:4.418ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \displaystyle f(x)}"></span>
</p>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \displaystyle f(x)=\|Ax-b\|^{2},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
          <mi>f</mi>
          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">‖<!-- ‖ --></mo>
          <mi>A</mi>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
          <mi>b</mi>
          <msup>
            <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">‖<!-- ‖ --></mo>
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mn>2</mn>
            </mrow>
          </msup>
          <mo>,</mo>
        </mstyle>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \displaystyle f(x)=\|Ax-b\|^{2},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/60d572c15c22c628df4495be5d546cfc086b82d7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:18.453ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \displaystyle f(x)=\|Ax-b\|^{2},}"></span></dd></dl></dd></dl>
<p>the minimum of <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle f}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>f</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle f}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/132e57acb643253e7810ee9702d9581f159a1c61" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:1.279ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle f}"></span> is obtained when the <a href="/wiki/Gradient" title="Gradient">gradient</a> is 0:
</p>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \nabla _{x}f=2A^{T}(Ax-b)=0}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi mathvariant="normal">∇<!-- ∇ --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>x</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mn>2</mn>
        <msup>
          <mi>A</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>T</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
        <mi>b</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mn>0</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \nabla _{x}f=2A^{T}(Ax-b)=0}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c847eded933aecc60394b06c4d16b34c6c26448e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:24.761ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \nabla _{x}f=2A^{T}(Ax-b)=0}"></span>.</dd></dl></dd></dl>
<p>Whereas linear conjugate gradient seeks a solution to the linear equation 
<span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \displaystyle A^{T}Ax=A^{T}b}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
          <msup>
            <mi>A</mi>
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mi>T</mi>
            </mrow>
          </msup>
          <mi>A</mi>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mo>=</mo>
          <msup>
            <mi>A</mi>
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mi>T</mi>
            </mrow>
          </msup>
          <mi>b</mi>
        </mstyle>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \displaystyle A^{T}Ax=A^{T}b}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/20f09e8944e61d70747b66b683d89270fc6cca6c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:13.434ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \displaystyle A^{T}Ax=A^{T}b}"></span>, the nonlinear conjugate gradient method is generally 
used to find the <a href="/wiki/Maxima_and_minima" class="mw-redirect" title="Maxima and minima">local minimum</a> of a nonlinear function 
using its <a href="/wiki/Gradient" title="Gradient">gradient</a> <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \nabla _{x}f}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi mathvariant="normal">∇<!-- ∇ --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>x</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mi>f</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \nabla _{x}f}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/216e7441a6ee87810c6172c158950217d5205837" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:4.387ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \nabla _{x}f}"></span> alone. It works when the function is approximately quadratic near the minimum, which is the case when the function is twice differentiable at the minimum and the second derivative is non-singular there.
</p><p>Given a function <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \displaystyle f(x)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
          <mi>f</mi>
          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        </mstyle>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \displaystyle f(x)}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/70218579209d1273fe59d0d5778f61a4a4597dc8" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:4.418ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \displaystyle f(x)}"></span> of <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle N}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>N</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle N}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f5e3890c981ae85503089652feb48b191b57aae3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.064ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle N}"></span> variables to minimize, its gradient <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \nabla _{x}f}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi mathvariant="normal">∇<!-- ∇ --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>x</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mi>f</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \nabla _{x}f}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/216e7441a6ee87810c6172c158950217d5205837" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:4.387ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \nabla _{x}f}"></span> indicates the direction of maximum increase.
One simply starts in the opposite (<a href="/wiki/Steepest_descent" class="mw-redirect" title="Steepest descent">steepest descent</a>) direction:
